i can remember the moment as af if it had just happened. i had just gotten home from my math tutor. i was in my parents room trying on my new soccer boots. fresh out the box and lookin good for the new high skool season. then my dad walks in and says. your not on the list. being on the team last year this was surely a joke. he looked at me again with a tear in his eye. i cant joke about this he said. we all stood there in silence, in shock, not beleiving what was just happening. all i could hear was marvelous 3 blaring on my stereo down the hall in my room. i didnt noe what to do. i was in shock. i had to see for myself. i took my new boots off, set them down and slowly trodded down to the computer. i looked. 61, blank, 63, 64, 65. where was 62? i was 62. still in disbelief i walked up the stairs where my dad greeted me. he said i love you son. then we hugged for a minute or two in disbelief. the first thing i did was who did i tell? so i called steven sizemore. he would noe. but noe answer. so i called bryce. i told him i didnt make the squad. he said that that was messed up. i couldnt a gree more. then i broke into tears remembering the fun that i had had on the squad the year before. i sat there crying on the phone. he said hed let me go. then jon(kenny g) called in on the other line. i was still crying like a girl when he called. i didnt noe what he thought but when i stold him what happened he was in utter shock. he said something was wrong and that there was a mistake and wed talk 2 coach and it would be ok. then i called austin. he was as blown away as everyone else. i sat trying to figure out my math homework that i had just mastered. i had forgotten everything. just blank still in denial. i kept thinking what am i to do? steven called. i told him he said that i had to be joking. untill he looked for himself he didnt belive me. he said that he would come with me and jon to talk 2 coach in the morning. morning came. i got to skool early just like jon and steven said they would. but time passed and no show. the bell rang for class. i had 2 do this on my own. this was the hardest thing in my life. i walked down the locker room hall and saw carpenter walking with gassman. my heart had to have skipped a beat. i said coach i didnt make it did i? he said no. i said can we talk he said sure. so we stepped in to his office. his comments were that i was a good kid and a good player. he said that this year was the hardest job of cuts he had ever made. he said that compared to the other sophomores i lacked skill that they had. he said the freshmen were too good and that i would just sit on the bench. i thought how could i got from starter last year to nothing? he said it may hurt now but itll be better than sitting. i said thanks and left in pure sadness. i was going to be sick. i called my dad and he came and checked me out of skool. i dont want to be seen at skool. im a discgrace to myself. id rather not even talk about this horrible moment in my my. collins hill meant the world to me soccer meant the world to me. my dreams were shattered in an instant. and it hurts so bad knowing that i could have done something about it. the people who made the team this year were the same people i play with at club soccer. my skill is just as good as theirs. yes some are better but im not a push over. i have skill. and i had dreams. but they are gone. and i dont noe what it will take to get them back. soccer was life for me. i didnt noe any other way and other choice. i wanted to live it. i wanted to keep the legacy going and feel like a part of something. but now all i have to look foreward to is sitting in the stands cheering my friends on as they play for what i wanted to. i told steven if he took my old #7 i would be honored. you dont noe what that number means to me. i have been number 7 all my life. my dream was to play soccer professionally. but now all of that is going away and it hurts sooooo much you dont even undertand. i am going to miss my passion so much. sometimes dreams dont come true.

YO HOMIES!!!!!!!! man i got back from chicago like 2 hours ago. lemme tell ya that was the frikin bomb. man the flight there was badassed cuz we were like in turbulance the whole time and like up and down it was fun. then when we arrived at the airport around 10 pm or so. they had those moving walkways and like i ran on em and then like almost flipped when i got off them. it rocked. :) then we took this thing 2 our airport and it was kool cuz we like cruised by the lake.(michigan) o man i completely forgot the view from the plane! it was spectacualar flying into the city with all of its lights on. it was beaautiful! man o man.our hotel was nice. cept our floor smelled like someone exploded vomit all over. yea gross. well then we woke up early the next day (friday)went 2 breakfast. then we went 2 the field museum. it wasnt bad my dad was really into it so we went. i was bored most of the time tho. we ate lunch lunch at mcdonalds by the lake and there were birds everywhere. so of course they like attacked the french fries. they had a sign that said no feeding the birds so what did i do? i fed the birds. it was pimp.then since the stadium 4 the soccer game was across the street we went 2 check it out and with ourluck we got 2 go into this adidas thing and watch bayern munich training. o man like front row it was badassed! then they gave us free shit 4 comin so yea. so after that we like went to our hotel and then walked around for a frikin hour 2 try anf find some place 2 eat. but we didnt so we ate ice cream 4 dinner. not bad. then the next day (saturday) we weoke up early again. ate breakfast. then went 2 the aquarium. it was supposed 2 be better than the tennessee but i beg 2 differ. it wasnt 2 hot. but again i was tired and my feet hurt so im lame.then after that we went 2 the planetarium. it was sooooo boring o man. i fell asleep like 2 times. then we went back 2 our hotel and went out 2 eat again. we went 2 the cheesecake factory. wow was that place huge. like massive and the food was great. the cheesecake on the other hand was below par which was surpising considering thats y theyre famous. w/e. so then we went 2 the nike town store. nice place man like 5 floors of stuff. i bought a shirt for the game the next day. i needed a little memorabilia. then off 2 the hancock building. we went 2 the 94th floor. we were higher than a dude after 3 joints man. it was crazed. then we got in the elevator back down and these german people snorted when they laughed. sweeeet. so then we went home and i talked on the fone 4 like ever. hope it wasnt roaming cuz if it was im in some shit. then i went 2 bed. the next day was game day. the day ive waited for forever. the day the greatest team on earth battled my favorite team. needless 2 say people thought an asswhoopin was in for my boys but, i proudly wore their jersey hoping great defeat would not come. and we won! oliver kahn is the man. my idol. my hero. 2 blocked penalty kicks is unheard of. especially against the greatest team on earth. o my it was amazing. if u wanna see the game come over i recorded it. then after the game it was a mob scene with 60,000 people leaving the stadium. yeah people stole boxes from the booths selling stuff so we bought some hot merchandide 4 like 15 bucks. nice. then we walked frikin like 3 miles back 2 our hotel. then we went out 2 this place suuuuper fancy man. i broke my all time dinner price. my dinner was 49.99 wow. it was soooo good tho. the steak melted in my mouth. my crab wasnt 2 great so i ate my dads fish and the rest of my moms steak and then some mashed taters and asparagus. it was good. then 4 dessert we had raspberry chocolate cake. yeah our check ended up at like 160$ for 3 people. then we went back 2 the hotel and packed. and rode the elevator. fun. strangely enough my dad ended up on the floor next 2 me sleeping/snoring like a bear.wierd. he did have a beer at dinner. then this morning we checked out. and went 2 this sporting goods store. my mom said shed get me sumthin nice so awesome. so we went and i got some new soccer boots. (predator pulse trx fg silver) ooh theyre pritty. and for only like 165$ and she gave me a free bag 2. nice lady. then we walked back 2 the hotel and got our bags and got in our shuttle back 2 the airport. o man that dude was psycho. he drove like 70 mph down the streets taking turns at 40. he almost hit 3 people. our luggage was flying around in the back. then we got onto the highway. of course rush hour. but not for this guy he wove through traffic like a granny in a knitting contest. i was scared. real scared. but i didnt die neither did my folks so its good. its goooood. yeah the plane ride sucked we had a bunch of smelly people from like pakistan er sumthin. yeah. now that im back i feel good. i miss it a bit tho. it was nice real nice. not ghetto either. great place 2 visit u should sometime. i give it a good rating. not nearly as kool as california but hey. it seems like a long dream tho but i have proof. so yea. well im out laterdays.

                             <3 shawnypoo
